    <p>Candy People Swedish Sour Skulls bring authentic Scandinavian candy engineering to the sour gummy category. Sweden consumes more candy per capita than any other country in the world — a cultural phenomenon called "lördagsgodis" (Saturday candy) — and Swedish confectioners have refined gummy formulations over generations. These sour skulls use a potato starch and pectin gelling system that is completely gelatin-free, producing a firm, snappy texture that is distinctly different from American-style pectin gummies. The sour coating is aggressive — more intense than Haribo and approaching Sour Patch Kids territory — with a citric-malic acid blend that Scandinavian brands have perfected. The skull shape adds a fun, slightly edgy visual element that sets them apart on a candy shelf. The main drawback is price: at $4.99 for a 4-ounce bag, they are the most expensive option on this list. But for candy enthusiasts who want to experience the Swedish approach to sour gummy craft, Candy People delivers an experience unavailable from domestic brands.</p>

