    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="faq-sec">
      <h2>Sour Gummies — Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <details class="fq"><summary>What makes sour gummies sour?</summary><p>Sour gummies get their tang from food-grade acids — primarily citric acid (sharp, immediate sourness), malic acid (smoother, longer-lasting), and tartaric acid (deeper, wine-like tartness). The sour sugar coating delivers the initial hit, while acids mixed into the gummy base sustain the tart flavor as you chew.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Are sour gummies bad for your teeth?</summary><p>Sour gummies are more damaging to tooth enamel than regular gummies because the acid coating lowers mouth pH to around 2.5 — below the 5.5 threshold for enamel erosion. Rinse with water immediately after eating and wait 30 minutes before brushing. The ADA recommends limiting sour candy consumption frequency.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>What are the sourest gummies you can buy?</summary><p>Among mainstream brands, Sour Patch Kids and Trolli Sour Brite Crawlers deliver the highest sour intensity. For extreme sourness, specialty brands like Barnetts Mega Sour offer dramatically higher acid concentrations, but these are novelty products.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Are there sugar-free sour gummies?</summary><p>Yes. SmartSweets Sour Blast Buddies and SmartSweets Sour Gummy Bears both contain only 3g sugar per bag using allulose and stevia. Most other mainstream sour gummies contain 20-28g of sugar per serving.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Are Sour Patch Kids vegan?</summary><p>Sour Patch Kids are gelatin-free (using modified corn starch), but they are not formally vegan-certified. The sugar may be processed with bone char. For certified vegan sour gummies, choose SmartSweets, Surf Sweets, or YumEarth.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Do sour gummies have gelatin?</summary><p>It depends on the brand. Haribo Sour, Albanese Sour, Black Forest Sour, and Trolli all contain gelatin. Sour Patch Kids, SmartSweets, YumEarth, Surf Sweets, and Candy People are gelatin-free.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>What is the best organic sour gummy?</summary><p>YumEarth Organic Sour Beans for best value and Surf Sweets Organic Sour Worms for broadest allergen protection. Both are USDA Organic with real fruit juice and no synthetic ingredients.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>How should I store sour gummies to keep them fresh?</summary><p>Store in a cool, dry place at 60-72 degrees Fahrenheit. Avoid direct sunlight and heat. Reseal bags tightly or use an airtight container. Do not refrigerate — condensation dissolves the sour coating. Shelf life is 6-12 months unopened.</p></details>
    </section>

